<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4915] Deserializing double into OrderedFloat always returns zero when using TCompactProtocol</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4915</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Client: Rust + Thrift 0.12.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Server: CPP + Thrift 0.9.3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Protocol: TCompactProtocol&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Transport: TBufferedTransport&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I logged before cpp server response to rust client&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;age=21.339611053466797&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;but client recieved&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
age: Some(OrderedFloat(0.))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This bug only happens when using TCompactProtocol.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
